Giovanni‚Äôs team had a refresh in Pok√©mon Go following the arrival of the summer ‚ÄúAdventure Week: Taken Over‚Äù event.

For those who want to catch Shadow Cresselia, try to get it done sooner than later, as there will likely be another Team Rocket refresh in coming months that‚Äôll swap out the legendary for a new one.

However, know that whenever you face Giovanni, he‚Äôs a tough opponent to battle, and this page will list out his current team and counters if you‚Äôre having trouble.

How to find Giovanni in Pok√©mon Go

Team Go Rocket boss Giovanni is typically only available to battle while completing Team Go Rocket Special Research. We get a new set of this type of research every few months, typically with a new Shadow legendary Pok√©mon as a reward at the very end.

From early August 2024, this quest is ‚ÄúAdventure Week: Taken Over.‚Äù

As part of the quest, after beating all three Team Go Rocket leaders, you‚Äôll get a Super Rocket Radar, allowing you to hunt down Giovanni.

Just like the leaders, Giovanni will appear in Team Go Rocket balloons or at taken over Pok√©Stops with the Super Rocket Radar equipped. He won‚Äôt often be in the first you encounter ‚Äî there will be decoy grunts along the way ‚Äî but keep trying and Giovanni will appear.

Once you find him and use the radar, you can battle him as many times as it takes to beat him ‚Äî as long as you‚Äôre within distance of the Pok√©Stop ‚Äî which is great, because he is typically a pretty tough battle.

Pok√©mon Go Giovanni counters

Because there are fewer potential party options for Giovanni than there are for the Rocket leaders, he‚Äôs actually easier to plan against, even if his Pok√©mon are much stronger. You will need to bring the strongest Pok√©mon you have, and your A-game in order to take him down.

How to beat Giovanni in Pok√©mon Go

As with fighting the leaders, Giovanni will block the first two charged attacks with shields. As such, you‚Äôll ideally want a fighting-type that can chip away at Persian‚Äôs health, while also having charged moves to destroy these two shields as fast as possible. From there, it‚Äôs a case of switching to the counters which suit the line-up that follows.

After defeating Giovanni, you will get to catch whichever Shadow legendary appears in the final encounter. It‚Äôs a guaranteed catch, so don‚Äôt forget to use a Pinap Berry to score some extra candy.

Finally, know that winning against Giovanni is an efficient way of earning Shadow Shards for Purified Gems, with each battle rewarding four Shards ‚Äî enough to make one Gem.
